      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "I was using to compare the current configuration with equals, after reading again from the file. @Data implements the equals, along with hash code and setters for non final fields.\n@RequiredArgsConstructor would replace the @AllArgsConstructor as all the fields are required.\nWe could only add the equals here, but for me this is a good candidate for a @Data object.\nAnd, in the current version, I'm not using equals anymore, but it is a good practice to have it, along with the hash code.\nI see no harm in keeping it as @Data. What do you think?",
